      "side": 1,
      "message": "This method is a good general set of basic tests.\n\nUsually for unit tests it\u0027s worth adding separate tests for each public method in the interface. So you might have separate test methods for Add, Get, RemoveRun. And you might even have separate test methods for different cases for each, like adding a url/rec that already exists, getting a rec that doesn\u0027t exist, etc. Some of these are already in your meta test here.\n\nThe idea is that then if something breaks and there\u0027s a failure the unit test error will be in a specific named method whose name makes it clear what test case exactly is broken. Seeing a failure in a method named TestGetOnEmptyResultStore will be clearer than seeing a failure in TestResultStore at line 80.\n\nAll that said I am less familiar with Go unit testing and in particular the style used in skia infra projects, so following those is also important.",
